  "prompt": "What is the best interview questions asked by you ?",
  "response": "As an AI language model, I don't participate in interviews or ask questions directly. However, I can suggest some commonly regarded effective interview questions that employers often use to assess candidates' skills, experience, and cultural fit. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. **Tell me about yourself.**\n   - This open-ended question allows candidates to introduce themselves and highlight their key skills and experiences.\n\n2. **What are your greatest strengths and weaknesses?**\n   - This question helps assess a candidate's self-awareness and ability to reflect on their personal development.\n\n3. **Describe a challenging situation you faced at work and how you dealt with it.**\n   - This behavioral question aims to gauge problem-solving skills and resilience.\n\n4. **Why do you want to work here?**\n   - This question tests whether the candidate has researched the company and aligns with its values and goals.\n\n5. **Where do you see yourself in five years?**\n   - This question helps determine a candidate's career goals and ambition.\n\n6. **Can you give an example of a project you led and the outcome?**\n   - This question assesses leadership skills and the ability to drive projects to completion.\n\n7. **How do you prioritize tasks when you have multiple deadlines?**\n   - This question evaluates time management and organizational skills.\n\n8. **Tell me about a time you failed and what you learned from it.**\n   - This question is designed to understand how a candidate handles failure and learns from mistakes.\n\n9. **How do you handle criticism?**\n   - This question explores a candidate's openness to feedback and ability to improve.\n\n10. **Do you have any questions for us?**\n    - This allows candidates to express interest in the role and gain clarity on aspects of the job or company.\n\nThese questions are intended to provide a comprehensive view of a candidate's capabilities and fit within a team. Tailoring questions to the specific role and company culture is always recommended for the best outcomes.",
